snippet.textDisplay:
Oh. China just unveiled why having facial recognition/data tracking could have a huge impact on the world and not in the hugely intrusive way everyone thinks. If you know, based on factual evidence that you've been exposed to a virus that could theoretically kill millions of people, including yourself, why would you not want to know that information? Not only can you take measures to either be checked for the disease or to see how you can protect yourself from it, but you can see how it's going to impact life around you. We take personal privacy for granted, even though, in all that's pretty much quantifiable, that privacy doesn't exist, except for a very few. 
For all the negatives there are about this topic, this app could very well mean what we all have to live with in the future. Staying alive, but nothing except our thoughts are private.
Unless you connect to Neuralink. Wonder what Elon is going to do about that...
